info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 14 at 3:18PM MST until February 15 at 2:00AM MST by NWS Phoenix
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 AM MST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 60 to 65 mph expected. * WHERE...Superior, Pinal/Superstition Mountains and Dripping Springs. * WHEN...Until 2 AM MST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Very difficult driving conditions, especially for larger vehicles traveling along roads with crosswinds. Light, unsecured objects will become airborne. Moderate tree and minor structural damage possible.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage. In addition, strong winds over desert areas could result in briefly lowered visibilities to well under a mile at times in blowing dust or blowing sand. Use extra caution.
